cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image categorization and scene recognition using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
